From ea92c7a50d7058475559790717fceef975325a4c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Simon Marlow <marlowsd@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 15:17:01 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Fix BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON: remove circular dependency (#692)

Summary:
Followup to https://github.com/facebook/fbthrift/issues/690, that PR inadvertently added a circular dependency between the thrifttype and thriftanyrep libraries, which means the `BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON` build still fails. This should fix it.

Tested with a PR on the hsthrift repo: https://github.com/facebookincubator/hsthrift/pull/174

Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/facebook/fbthrift/pull/692

Reviewed By: Mizuchi

Differential Revision: D96944523

Pulled By: iahs

fbshipit-source-id: ecb75e972d7d074eff1f44c29ba0960ca8416970
---
 thrift/lib/cpp2/CMakeLists.txt | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/thrift/lib/cpp2/CMakeLists.txt b/thrift/lib/cpp2/CMakeLists.txt
index 78b2066a5e9..5b7e4eafbd0 100644
--- a/thrift/lib/cpp2/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/thrift/lib/cpp2/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -231,7 +231,6 @@ target_link_libraries(
     common
     Folly::folly
     thriftannotation
-    thriftanyrep
     thrifttyperep
     thriftprotocol
 )
